summary: What irks me most about Count Dooku is that almost all portrayals stop at the racist Sith Lord who wanted to destroy all to...
question: What irks me most about Count Dooku is that almost all portrayals stop at the racist Sith Lord who wanted to destroy all to build it anew and then with only humans in charge. There are some EU materials which show Dooku before his contact and falling in with Sidious and back then he was largely a noble man who attempted for several years to get both the Jedi Council and the Senate to act and reform via talking and diplomacy alone. Yet no one heeded his warnings and advice and he went radical.
answer: Okay. I’m not really familiar with the old EU, so I really can’t comment on that. In the actual Clone Wars though, there really isn’t anything about him which screams anti-human. All of his top generals are non-human and he actually seems to have a pretty decent working relationship with them.

summary: Listening to the Star Wars soundtracks while you do everyday, normal shit like make a sandwich or check your email is just the...
body: Listening to the Star Wars soundtracks while you do everyday, normal shit like make a sandwich or check your email is just the wildest thing.  It’s like “This sandwich, which is clearly the most important sandwich in the galaxy, has the power to shift the balance in the Force!” or “Checking this email will take me one step closer to my destiny as the leader of the Jedi Order!”

summary: Legends Of The Hydian Way - The Phantom Menace
title: Legends Of The Hydian Way - The Phantom Menace
body:
Legends Of The Hydian Way – The Phantom Menace

We have, at long last, reached the first film in the Star wars franchise. 20,000 years of galactic history in under a year ain’t bad! Today we’re looking back at the novelization of The Phantom Menace. I plan to take a slightly different approach to the film novelizations in this project. Since most of you reading this have seen the films, I’m going to be focusing more on where the novels differ.…

blog.name: mandowords
blog.title: Miit'alor
blog.description: I am a descriptivist linguist for the Mando'a language. I show what it can do, not what it MUST do. This is a place for discussion about Mando'a, and Mandalorian society and culture. Feel free to use the head cannons from this blog (or reblogged from others) in your RP or writing. All words and descriptions are taken from the mandoa.org Mandalorian Dictionary. Want to support this blog? Buy me a Kofi? OR buy some Mando'a themed items? Visit our Discord? Blog icon by Rina
